<br>
The cheapest horses (the 8-10kpp ones) are slightly faster than nonsow, non aa skill runspeed, but slower than jboots/run3.<br>
<br>
For speed really only the 100k+ ones are good.<br>
<br>
You will always regen mana on a horse if you are:<br>
a) not moving<br>
b) not melee'ing<br>
You regen hitpoints as if standing, but regen mana as if sitting, you med even if you are casting a spell, you do not get the normal sit aggro, dont have to stand up to send in pet to avoid aggro.<br>
<br>
You cannot, however duck to interupt spells, unless you have models off.<br>
To use horse you must EITHER have your race model and horse/elemental model on, OR ALL models off, in which case you can use horse without seeing it, you can duck to interupt spell, you can run at sow speed if you have it on, you start and stop instant, without the delay.<br>
In fact I havent used new models in a while, cuz its so nice to use horse without 'em...<br>
<br>
All in all the cheapest horse is a great investment, just dont expect to be able to use it to move faster, or when pulling. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99814" target="top">Master Appren Hightowerr</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
